<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ice" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ice,</orth> congealed water: <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.123" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 226</bibl>. Symbol of coldness: <cit><quote>boys of i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls II, 3, 99</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou art all i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 2, 22</bibl></cit>. of chastity: <cit><quote>the very i. of chastity is in them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 4, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as chaste as i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.140" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 140</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>icicle</emph> in <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 65</bibl>). <emph>to break the ice</emph> == to open the way: <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.267" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 267</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 215</bibl>. <emph>to smooth the i.</emph> == to do a thing superfluous: <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 13</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>